editorialSummary.text: Casual guesthouse offering 4 warm rooms with smart TVs, plus a lounge with a piano.

originalText.text: Really great converted Brownstone in a really vibrant part of Harlem. The owners are friendly and really helpful but also give you privacy unless you need them. The  rooms vary, as it is converted Brownstone, but are comfortable with private bathooms. They are not overly fancy but tastefully done and comfortable  There is a large very well equipped kitchen and a grocery store nearby so it is an excellent place to stay if you want to save money by cooking yourself. It is a short and safe walk to the subway and the Apollo theater.

originalText.text: The Gino Room is excellently suited to 2 or 3 guests. The host went completely out of his way to be helpful and kind to us before, during, and after our stay (we forgot an item and he was beyond his obligations in helping us retrieve it). I absolutely recommend the 255 Guest House if you're looking for a centrally located, wonderful place to stay in Harlem!

originalText.text: My daughter and I stayed at 255West Guesthouse. We were in the Gulliame room. Loved the room and bathroom. We had everything we needed. The towels were soft and absorbent. We loved the availability of the full kitchen even though we didn't use it. The subway was easily accessible and we felt safe at all hours of the day walking to and from. We enjoyed stopping at the Lenox coffeehouse for breakfast and a latte on our walk to the subway. Our flights came in around 0900 into LaGuardia and we we're at the guest house within 30 minutes. James greeted is and we we're able to stash our bags and begin our day! Loved every second staying there and will stay again next time we go to NYC!
